claim.claim-text:
1. A head slider having a disk opposing surface, an air inlet end, and an air outlet end, said head slider comprising: 
a front rail formed on said disk opposing surface in the vicinity of said air inlet end, said front rail having a first air bearing surface and a first step surface lower in level than said first air bearing surface; 
a transducer formed in the vicinity of said air outlet end; 
a first groove for expanding air once compressed by said front rail to generate a negative pressure; and 
a second groove formed on said first step surface near said air inlet end except opposite side portions of said first step surface; 
said first step surface reaching said air inlet end at said opposite side portions.

4. A head slider having a disk opposing surface, an air inlet end, and an air outlet end, said head slider comprising: 
a front rail formed on said disk opposing surface in the vicinity of said air inlet end, said front rail having a first air bearing surface and a first step surface lower in level than said first air bearing surface; 
a transducer formed in the vicinity of said air outlet end; 
a first groove for expanding air once compressed by said front rail to generate a negative pressure; and 
a pair of second grooves formed on said first step surface near said air inlet end except a laterally central portion of said first step surface; 
said first step surface reaching said air inlet end 
at said laterally central portion.

8. A disk drive comprising: 
a housing having a base; 
a negative pressure type head slider having a transducer for reading/writing data from/to a disk having a plurality of tracks, an air inlet end, and an air outlet end, and a disk opposing surface; 
an actuator for moving said negative pressure type head slider across said tracks of said disk; 
means for controlling said actuator to load/unload said negative pressure type head slider to/from said disk; and 
a ramp member fixed to said base for supporting said negative pressure type head slider unloaded from said disk; 
said actuator comprising: 
an actuator arm rotatably mounted on said base; 
a suspension fixed at a base end portion thereof to a front end portion of said actuator arm; and 
said negative pressure type head slider mounted on a front end portion of said suspension; 

said negative pressure type head slider comprising: 
a front rail formed on said disk opposing surface in the vicinity of said air inlet end, said front rail having a air bearing surface and a step surface lower in level than said air bearing surface; 
a transducer formed in the vicinity of said air outlet end; 
a first groove for expanding air once compressed by said front rail to generate a negative pressure; and 
a second groove formed on said step surface near said air inlet end except opposite side portions of said step surface; 

said step surface reaching said air inlet end at said opposite side portions.

9. A disk drive comprising: 
a housing having a base; 
a negative pressure type head slider having a transducer for reading/writing data from/to a disk having a plurality of tracks, an air inlet end, and an air outlet end, and a disk opposing surface; 
an actuator for moving said negative pressure type head slider across said tracks of said disk; 
means for controlling said actuator to load/unload said negative pressure type head slider to/from said disk; and 
a ramp member fixed to said base for supporting said negative pressure type head slider unloaded from said disk; 
said actuator comprising: 
an actuator arm rotatably mounted on said base; 
a suspension fixed at a base end portion thereof to a front end portion of said actuator arm; and 
said negative pressure type head slider mounted on a front end portion of said suspension; 

said negative pressure type head slider comprising: 
a front rail formed on said disk opposing surface in the vicinity of said air inlet end, said front rail having a air bearing surface and a step surface lower in level than said air bearing surface; 
a transducer formed in the vicinity of said air outlet end; 
a first groove for expanding air once compressed by said front rail to generate a negative pressure; and 
a pair of second grooves formed on said step surface near said air inlet end except a laterally central portion of said step surface; 

said step surface reaching said air inlet end at said laterally central portion.
